HEADWORD: Pelisse
<hw>Pe*lisse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>pelliceus</ets>, <ets>pellicius</ets>, made of skins, fr.
<ets>pellis</ets> a skin. Cf. <er>Pelt</er> skin, <er>Pilch</er>, and
see 2d <er>Pell</er>.]</ety> <def>An outer garment for men or women,
originally of fur, or lined with fur; a lady's or child's long outer
garment, made of silk or other fabric.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pell</ent>⟦br⟧
